<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,474,500]" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Ahrens, Fabrizi &amp; Liu" authorityName="Ahrens, Fabrizi &amp; Liu" authorityYear="2021" box="[328,846,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Maladera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maguanensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[328,591,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">Maladera maguanensis</emphasis>
Ahrens, Fabrizi &amp; Liu
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[856,916,475,501]" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Ahrens, Fabrizi &amp; Liu" authorityName="Ahrens, Fabrizi &amp; Liu" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Maladera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lushanensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1062,1230,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">M. lushanensis</emphasis>
Ahrens, Fabrizi &amp; Liu
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[204,263,511,537]" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in having the parameres slightly longer and the apex of the phallobase flat dorsally; as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ahrens" authorityYear="2004" box="[1265,1389,511,536]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Maladera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="siniaevi">
<emphasis box="[1265,1389,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">M. siniaevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Ahrens, 2004" authorityName="Ahrens" authorityYear="2004" box="[151,426,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Maladera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tumida">
<emphasis box="[151,267,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="180" pageNumber="181">M. tumida</emphasis>
Ahrens, 2004
</taxonomicName>
, the left paramere has a lateral carina.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1417,583,610]" pageId="180" pageNumber="181" type="etymology">
